image:
Good luck to all of the Spectrum MX racers! We are honored and thankful to be working with Spectrum MX.

Spectrum MX added a new photo to the album: SMX News.
June 11, 2019 at 12:38 PM ·

We are loving our new Spectrum MX trucker hats!

Available now to all family and friends. Beanies are coming soon for colder race weekends and of course our winter Ice Racing months!

Each of our riders will be receiving their choice of either a hat or a beanie. Friends and Family who would like to order their own hat may do so through Race Graphics Plus.

Thank you to Ken and his crew for taking the time in helping us get everything set up for nationals next year!

Dew N Jenna Millhisler
Tyler Gregg

Spectrum MX added a new photo to the album: Trey Millhisler #104 — with Trey Man Millhisler.
April 18, 2019 at 4:32 PM ·

Check out Trey Man’s 2019 MX machine! Want to give a HUGE shout out to Next Level Graphic & Design. You guys are one of the ones who have supported Trey from the beginning. Not only do you know him on the track, but you know him as a person. You all see on the gas tank above our logo, Never, Never Give Up.... Trey has been telling us that since he we 4 years old. That saying being on the gas tank was all David Smith, and you have no idea how special it was for us to see it on there. You guys are truly the best!

On this Thanksgiving we say thank you to all of our great customers. We love the support that our Coleman community and surrounding communities have given us.

I personally have to give thanks my family for their full support, Sharon Harnick my mother in law for all of her help every afternoons. She is becoming really good friends with the embroidery machine.

Also thankful that we were able to bring Annabelle Bovee on. She has been doing a tremendous job and is willing to do whatever is asked of her. Thank you Annabelle for being willing to learn and bring a lot of laughs to the day.

Again we thank all of you , we are truly blessed.

HAPPY THANKSGIVING!!!!

One year ago today we officially opened the store. I want to say thank you to each and every person that has stopped in and supported us. We have been fortunate enough to have been able to help several Non profits, fundraisers, clubs, teams, schools and businesses in the area. Your business is greatly appreciated.
With that said I can’t thank Jackie, Tyler, and Lexi enough for the support. Everyone knows that starting a business from the ground up
Is not easy, I will admit at times I wanted to call it quits and find a 9-5 job. They keep me grounded and focused. Also a huge thank to Sharon Harnick for helping me out every day any way she can.
Again THANK YOU to each and every one of you.
